.TH ZEDIT 1 "2026-02-17" "zedit 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zedit \- modern console text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zedit
.RI [ file ]
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-help
.br
.B zedit
.B \-\-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Zedit
is a modern console text editor written in pure Rust
with zero external dependencies. It features UTF\-8 native text handling,
modern desktop\-style keybindings (Ctrl+C/V/X/S/Z), syntax highlighting
via TextMate grammars, and diff\-based rendering for smooth performance.
Part of the Z ecosystem (Zenith, Zymbol).
.PP
If
.I file
is given, it is opened for editing. Otherwise a new empty buffer is created.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS File
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save file. If the buffer has no file name, prompts for one.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+S
Save As \(em prompts for a new file name.
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open file \(em prompts for a file path.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Q
Quit. If there are unsaved changes, press again to confirm.
.SS Edit
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Y
Redo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Copy selection (or current line if no selection).
.TP
.B Ctrl+X
Cut selection (or current line if no selection).
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste from clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+D
Duplicate current line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+K
Delete current line.
.TP
.B Tab
Insert indentation (spaces or tab character, depending on
.IR use_spaces
config option).
.TP
.B Shift+Tab
Unindent current line or selected lines.
.TP
.B Ctrl+/
Toggle line comment (language\-aware).
.TP
.B Enter
Insert newline with auto\-indent.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move cursor up/down/left/right.
.TP
.B Home / End
Move to start/end of line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Home / Ctrl+End
Move to start/end of file.
.TP
.B Page Up / Page Down
Scroll one page up/down.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Go to line number.
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Find (incremental search, case\-insensitive). Press Ctrl+R to toggle regex mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+H
Find and replace.
.TP
.B F3 / Shift+F3
Jump to next/previous search match.
.SS Selection
.TP
.B Shift+Arrow keys
Extend selection character by character or line by line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Left/Right
Extend selection word by word.
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select all.
.TP
.B Ctrl+L
Select current line.
.SS Multi\-buffer
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
Open a new empty buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Close current buffer (confirms if unsaved).
.TP
.B Ctrl+Page Down
Switch to next buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Page Up
Switch to previous buffer.
.SS Mouse
.TP
.B Click
Position cursor.
.TP
.B Drag
Select text.
.TP
.B Scroll wheel
Scroll viewport up/down.
.SS Help
.TP
.B F1
Toggle the in\-editor help overlay.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B Zedit
reads its configuration from
.IR ~/.config/zedit/config.json .
Example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{
    "tab_size": 4,
    "use_spaces": true,
    "theme": "zedit\-dark",
    "line_numbers": true,
    "auto_indent": true,
    "word_wrap": false,
    "languages": [
        {
            "name": "ruby",
            "extensions": ["rb", "rake"],
            "grammar": "ruby.tmLanguage.json",
            "comment": "#"
        }
    ]
}
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B tab_size
Number of spaces per indentation level (1\(en16, default 4).
.TP
.B use_spaces
If true (default), Tab inserts spaces. If false, inserts a literal tab character.
.TP
.B theme
Color theme name. Built\-in themes:
.BR zedit\-dark ", " zedit\-light .
Custom themes go in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/themes/ .
.TP
.B line_numbers
Show line number gutter (default true).
.TP
.B auto_indent
Preserve indentation on Enter (default true).
.TP
.B word_wrap
Wrap long lines visually (default false).
.TP
.B languages
Array of language definitions. Each entry has:
.BR name " (language identifier),"
.BR extensions " (file extension list),"
.BR grammar " (TextMate grammar filename),"
.BR comment " (line comment prefix, optional)."
User entries override built\-in languages by name; new names are appended.
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
.B Zedit
uses TextMate grammar files
.RB ( .tmLanguage.json )
for syntax highlighting. Built\-in grammars are provided for:
Rust, C, C++, Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, PHP, Shell, HTML, CSS,
JSON, TOML, Markdown, Zenith, and Zymbol.
.PP
User\-provided grammars can be placed in
.IR ~/.config/zedit/grammars/ .
The grammar filename must match the
.B grammar
field in the language definition.
.PP
Themes follow the VS Code color theme format. Color output adapts automatically
to the terminal's capabilities (24\-bit, 256\-color, or 16\-color).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/config.json
Editor configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/grammars/
User\-provided TextMate grammar files.
.TP
.I ~/.config/zedit/themes/
User\-provided color theme files.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B COLORTERM
If set to
.BR truecolor " or " 24bit ,
enables 24\-bit color output.
.TP
.B TERM
Used to detect 256\-color support (e.g.,
.BR xterm\-256color ).
Falls back to 16\-color mode otherwise.
.SH AUTHORS
Written as part of the Z ecosystem (Zenith, Zymbol).
